details: Extremely sought after for decades since its original release, the 1939 J-55 delivers an aura of sound with an incredible dynamic range, warm mids, and a tight punchy bass. It excels in the woody ambience good Gibson guitars are known for
features: Thermally Aged Red Spruce Vintage Sunburst Top
Traditional Advanced Hand-Scalloped Red Spruce Hide Glue Top Bracing
